Glassworm burrower queen extermination
-1 3 1 1 62 75 5760 5000 5 2000000 0
5769
The glassworm burrower queen has been expanding her tunnel network through the Glasswind Belt at a rate that is destabilizing the ancient glass formations and sealing off the Glasswalk Guide routes that families have used for generations. Individual worm encounters are manageable, but the queen's tunneling will render large sections of the Belt impassable within a season. The Glasswalk Guide elder requires her elimination before the route network can be restored.
The glassworm burrower queen has been destroyed and the network expansion has halted. Glasswalk Guide survey teams have confirmed that the most critical route corridors are stable and passable with standard precautions. The elder has issued updated route advisories and dispatched scouts to map the extent of the existing tunnel damage for seasonal remediation planning.

